# Workflow Protocol

## Session start

- Check `docs/decisions/` if the task touches business logic or prior decisions.
- Check `git log -10 --oneline` to understand recent context.
- If requirements are unclear or the task touches DB/auth/UX, use `grill-me` before proposing anything.

## When to use grill-me

| Task complexity | Action |
|----------------|--------|
| Simple — 1-2 files, no DB, no auth, no UX redesign | Implement directly. Brief proposal if non-trivial. |
| Medium — business logic, multi-file, existing patterns | `grill-me` → implement directly |
| Complex — DB, auth, multi-slice, new flows | `grill-me` → `slice` → implement per skill |

If unsure which category: default to `grill-me`. Cost is 5 minutes. Skipping it on complex tasks costs much more.

## Vertical slices

Work in minimal end-to-end slices (DB + logic + UI). Each slice must be independently verifiable before starting the next.

## Skills

| Task | Skill |
|------|-------|
| Alignment before feature work | `grill-me` |
| Decompose into ordered slices | `slice` |
| Backend queries, actions, RLS | `backend` |
| UI components, pages, design system | `frontend` |
| Final verification before declaring done | `done` |
| E2E validation of critical flows (manual) | `qa` |

`frontend` and `backend` run within an approved slice context. `done` always runs last. `qa` is manual — never automatic.

## Skill invocation

In Claude Code: use the `Skill` tool.
In Cursor: use the `skill` tool or `@skill-name`.
